# Void Music Player

VMP is a minimalist, keyboard-driven TUI music player designed for high-fidelity audio and distraction-free listening. Built with Go, it provides a "rice-friendly" alternative to complex setups like MPD.

## Controls

- [j/k]: Browse Folders
- [Enter]: Select & Play

- [p]: Play/Pause
- [b/n]: Prev/Next Track
- [e/r]: Seek 5s
- [s]: Toggle Shuffle

- [+/-]: Volume Control
- [q]: Quit

Keybinds are also shown inside the app if you forgot some :P

## Installation

For now you can do this:
Create a folder for vmp and put *.go files inside it.
Next, inside that folder, run "go install ." (without the quotation marks"
Unsure on how it works on Windows, but on Linux add "export PATH=$PATH:$(go env GOPATH)/bin" (without quotation marks) to your .bashrc or .zshrc.
Next, just run "vmp" inside your terminal and it should load.
VMP also check just the ~/Music folder, so I doubt it will work on Windows and it's possible it will work on Mac. If you use any other directory... it won't work.
